Defendant Sylvia Katarzyna Hass in court with attorney Brian Christopher Hagner.  Ian Franklin Vance-Curzan appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy Court Clerk ssm.  

Sentencing proceeded.  Statements by the State, defense and defendant.  

AS TO BOTH COUNTS:  Defendant sentenced to serve 3 MONTHS  in the House of Correction CONSECUTIVE to each other; credit for 4 days time served as to Count 1 only.  Huber privileges for work, treatment and school.  Court STAYED the sentence and placed defendant on Probation with the State of Wisconsin, Department of Corrections for a period of 24 MONTHS.
CONDITIONS AS TO BOTH COUNTS: 
*  AODA assessment/treatment deemed appropriate;
*  Obtain/maintain full time employment/school or a combination of both;
*  Maintain absolute sobriety;
*  Pay all costs and surcharges commencing September 15, 2016 at the rate of $25.00 per month or, if not paid, convert to a civil judgment.

CONDITIONS AS TO COUNT 1 ONLY:
*  Pay restitution in the amount of $99.92 to Walmart; cash bail on deposit to be applied;
*  Perform 20 hours of community service.
